Spanish, Chinese, and Japanese, subtitles included, DVD cover says special edition probably because of the former. There are no other extras.

This is a silent film and one of the only Hitchcock films where he doesn't do a cameo.

Slow to start but some HILARIOUS moments, this is Hitchcock at his very beginning.

One or two of the early text cells are faded but not my fault, this is the only DVD release of this film I could find and it doesn't affect the story.  If you pause it you can make them out.

